                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d356">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.00/310: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Riddle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-01T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 1, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>63. Department’s 51, September 30, 5 p.m. As special ambassadors are to be
                    received by President Irigoyen to whom letters of credence will be presented 2
                    or 3 days prior to date of inauguration the Argentine Government desires that
                    procedure be uniform in all cases and that letters be addressed to him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Riddle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
